sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Application
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant KServe as KServe InferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Storage as PVC/Database<br/>PostgreSQL/MySQL
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>80/8080 HTTP

    Note over User,Prom: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Model Prediction Monitoring

    User->>KServe: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token

    KServe->>TrustyAI: Prediction Data (ModelMesh Payload Processor)<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 80-443<br/>Auth: None

    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store Prediction & Metadata<br/>Filesystem or PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>TLS1.2+ (conditional)
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: ACK

    KServe-->>User: Prediction Result

    Prom->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Auth: None
    TrustyAI-->>Prom: Prometheus Metrics

    Note over User,Prom: Flow 2: LM Evaluation Job Execution

    participant API as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant LMEval as LMEvalJob Controller
    participant Kueue as Kueue API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Pod as LMES Pod
    participant HF as Hugging Face Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    User->>API: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    API-->>LMEval: Watch Event

    LMEval->>Kueue: Create Workload<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Kueue->>API: Schedule Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3

    API->>Pod: Start LMES Pod

    Pod->>HF: Download Model/Dataset<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: API Token (optional)
    HF-->>Pod: Model Artifacts

    Pod->>KServe: Inference Requests<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KServe-->>Pod: Predictions

    Pod->>S3: Store Evaluation Results<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM/Access Key
    S3-->>Pod: ACK

    Pod-->>API: Job Complete

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Guardrails Orchestrator Request Processing

    participant Client as External Client
    participant GRoute as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GOAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GOrch as Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS
    participant Detector as Detector InferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Generator as Generator InferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Client->>GRoute: POST /detect<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    GRoute->>GOAuth: OAuth Redirect
    GOAuth-->>Client: Login Page
    Client->>GOAuth: Auth Credentials
    GOAuth->>GOAuth: Validate Token

    GOAuth->>GOrch: Forwarded Request<br/>HTTPS/8032 TLS (service-ca)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token

    GOrch->>Detector: Content Detection<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Detector-->>GOrch: Detection Result

    alt Content Allowed
        GOrch->>Generator: Generate Response<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        Generator-->>GOrch: Generated Content
        GOrch-->>GOAuth: Response
    else Content Blocked
        GOrch-->>GOAuth: 403 Blocked
    end

    GOAuth-->>GRoute: Response
    GRoute-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over User,API: Flow 4: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Operator as Operator Controller
    participant CRWatch as CR Watch Stream<br/>TLS1.3

    API->>Operator: CR Change Event<br/>Watch Stream TLS1.3<br/>Auth: Service Account Token

    Operator->>API: Get CR Details<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    API-->>Operator: CR Spec

    Operator->>Operator: Reconcile Logic

    Operator->>API: Create/Update Resources<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3<br/>Deployments, Services, Routes, etc.
    API-->>Operator: Resource Created

    Operator->>API: Update CR Status<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3
    API-->>Operator: Status Updated
